> The deliciousness of an apple crumble but for breakfast! With cinnamon-spiced
> apples and crunchy granola, this breakfast makes for a special start to the
> morning.

Peel, quarter and core the @apples{2%unit(s)}.

Finely chop.

Add apples, @ground cinnamon{1%sachet}, 2 tbsp of @water{2%tbsp} and
@sugar{5%tsp} to a #medium pot{} over medium heat.

Cook until the apple begins to soften, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Set aside to cool, ~{5%minutes}.

Divide @yoghurt{220%g} between serving bowls.

Mix the @granola{120%g} through the apples.

To finish, spoon the yoghurt over the top.